Subject: DPAA NOTES/ DUE-OUTS

Team DPAA,

Happy Thursday! It’s been a TOUGH week and I’m looking forward to all of us taking some time tomorrow afternoon to let loose a bit and recognize our hails and farewells! Please see below for activities, notes from staff meeting, and Division due outs…

Activities:
• Today’s IHT CANCELLED in lieu of…..
o ARPC Promotion Ceremony! Tomorrow 26 August @ 1400 in the Summit to celebrate TSgt Collins promotion to MSgt!!
o Please join us after the ceremony for a late lunch at BJs to celebrate the promotion at 1515. Please email SMSgt Strickler to RSVP! 
• DPAA Hails & Farewells Offsite Friday 27 August at Main Event 1230-1730 (64 Centennial Blvd Highlands Ranch, CO 80129) DPAA leadership is covering tickets so please email SMSgt Strickler if you CAN NOT attend. This is considered an alternate duty location; if unable to attend, you must be working or on leave
• Rising 6 Burger Burn this Friday on the patio

DPAA Notes:
• Leave
o September is going to be a busy time for us as we close out the Fiscal Year.  However, I think its also important that our member’s continue to take leave within reason.  I define it as a balance between ensuring the continued mission and the time-off that you so deservingly earned.  My intent is not to close out / cancel leave during this timeframe, but I ask for your understanding and that you work with your direct supervisors and your Branch Chiefs/Superintendents to make that determination. 

DUE OUTS:
• TELEWORK AGREEMENTS must be accomplished by 1 September. Please see attachment, complete, and save on the N Drive at the following location…. N:\DPAA New Sharedrive folder\TELEWORK AGREEMENTS (TSgt Williams will be reviewing the agreements so if he contacts you, please work with him on corrections)

DPA Staff Meeting Notes:
• Last week of DPAA on break room cleanup. Please ensure we are remaining diligent with clean up!
• Please ensure members are wearing masks at all times if not eating or drinking and everyone is cleaning/sanitizing their sections daily
• In need of DPA volunteers and one lead with assisting Ms. Willett for the ARPC Thanksgiving extravaganza! Email SMSgt Strickler if interested
• Fitness testing- outdoors only

COVID Updates:
• Buckley is posturing for HPCON Bravo+ effective 30 Aug
• With Pfizer vaccine being FDA approved, SECDEF is drafting the policy requiring mandated vaccines for military members
o Limited exemption options:
? Religious reasons (requires MAJCOM approval; difficult to obtain)
? Medical reasons (must be approved by a military doctor)
? Admin reason (separating or retiring in 100 days)
• Gym will be limited access for vaccinated guests only
• Teleworking-all members must be prepared for a recall to the building at any time. Child care should no longer be an issue or an excuse to not return to the building when required. If there is any reason why a member is unable to come to the building when required (ie, medical issues/humanitarian reason) please contact SMSgt Strickler immediately. Temporary issues such as illness or quarantine do not count towards this. 

To wrap this up SMSgt Strickler needs RSVPs for Main Event and BJs, volunteers for Thanksgiving feast, and any telework issues preventing immediate recalls to the building.  We look forward to Friday afternoon’s off-site to see everyone’s smiling faces, recognize our hails, properly send off our farewells and just to come out and have some fun!!

-Harold

Good afternoon, 

DPTG is the primary OPR for the ARPC Commander’s Field Support (FSSE) line. We currently have a recorded message a caller hears when they dial (720) 847-3400 or DSN 847-3400. We want to add another recorded message in front of the current message with following verbiage:

Greetings, 

You have reached the Field Support Services Element. The purpose of this line is to assist General Officers, Commanders, Chiefs, and Executive Officers, to include FSS and CSS Superintendents, with benefit or pay affecting issues that must be resolved within 48 hours for assigned members. 

If you are General Officer, Commander, Chief or an FSS Superintendent calling with an urgent pay-effecting issue for a member within the scope of your supervision please press 1. If you are not an eligible caller, please contact the Total Force Service Center @1-800-525-0102 or submit a request via myPers @www.mypers.af.mil.

Thank you and have a nice day.

Goal - Upon pressing 1, the call routes to the current FSSE answering service or connects with live DPTG rep.  We would also like to explore the possibility that the call can automatically route to the TFSC SA 1-800 number if they dial 2. 

Please let me know if you need additional information or clarification or would to discuss in person. 

Thanks in advance,
